See A Curated Selection Design Features Unique to All Implants

Exclusive High-Strength Cohesive Gel

Engineered for shape retention and high resistance to fracture, while maintaining a remarkably soft feel.2

Flat Back Design

Allows implants to conform to the chest wall, creating a smooth lateral edge designed to limit palpability and wrinkling.

Gel Fill Level

Optimal fill ratio designed to provide and maintain the desired breast shape in combination with the slope of the chest wall.

Highest Level of Gel-Shell Integration2

Provides greater adherence of the gel fill to the shell, resulting in an implant that maintains both strength and softness.2

Exclusive High-Strength Cohesive Gel

Engineered for shape retention and high resistance to fracture, while maintaining a remarkably soft feel.2

Gel Fill Level

Optimal fill ratio designed to provide and maintain the desired breast shape in combination with the slope of the chest wall.

Flat Back Design

Allows implants to conform to the chest wall, creating a smooth lateral edge designed to limit palpability and wrinkling.

Highest Level of Gel-Shell Integration2

Provides greater adherence of the gel fill to the shell, resulting in an implant that maintains both strength and softness.2

Smooth Surface

Popular Choice

Soft yet durable, our smooth sheel aids in the natural feel of our implants. The shell is designed to minimize rupture and allow the implant to move naturally with the natural breast tissue.

MicrotexturedSurface

Textured Surfaces are Not All the Same

More rough and aggressive shell surfaces have been classified as macrotextured. Sientra’s textured shell has been classified as a microtexture due to its less aggressive, finer surface.3 Sientra’s microtextured surface has been reported to have the lowest number of BIA-ALCL (cancer of the immune system) cases of all U.S. implant brands.3,13

Sientra’s microtextured shell surface3 and exclusive High-Strength Cohesive Gel are clinically shown to have low rates of capsular contracture, rupture, and reoperation.1

Scanning electron microscopic (SEM) images of Sientra and Allergan textured surfaces at 65x magnification. SEM is the industry standard to characterize the combination of shell surface disruption and pores promoting tissue adherence to the textured shell surface.

Two Exclusive High-Strength Cohesive Gels, HSC & HSC+

Engineered for optimal shape retention and fracture resistance while maintaining a natural feel.

High-Strength Cohesive Gel (HSC)

  • Soft feel mimics natural breast tissue
  • Impressive upper pole retention
  • More resistant to gel fracture than competitive gels2
  • Designed to maintain a full, youthful look

Available on Round Implants

High-Strength Cohesive Gel Plus (HSC+)

  • More cohesive gel – firmer feel
  • Unmatched shape retention2
  • Highest level of gel fracture resistance available2
  • Designed to minimize wrinkling and rippling

Available on Round and Shaped Implants

See Strength and Softness

Sientra implants offer the highest level of gel fracture resistance available without the compromise of an overly firm implant.2

HSC & HSC+ implants show minimum trade-off in softness in order to achieve greater gel strength.2

Over 250 Round Implant Options

6 Projection Levels

low projection | (160 cc – 700 cc)

low-plus projection | (80 cc – 440 cc)

moderate projection | (190 cc – 700 cc)

moderate plus projection | (175 cc – 695 cc)

high projection | (190 cc – 700 cc)

Xtra high projection | (275 cc – 510 cc)

Over 90 TeardropShape Implant Options

2 Projection Levels

moderate projection | (160 cc – 700 cc)

high projection | (190 cc – 635 cc)

See Satisfaction

I am so happy I made this decision for myself. I look in the mirror and see the silhouette I’ve always wanted.

– SARITA
Actual Sientra Patient

The highest rated breast implant brand in the U.S.*

*Among silicone gel breast implants; As of March 14, 2025, realself.com
